When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

    When you wanted to share your code with others. It would also back up your
    code somewhere offsite.

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    Because you may be working on code and you don't want that overwritten
	before you have a chance to commit those changes.

